Glomerulocystic kidney
he term glomerulocystic kidney () refers to a kidney with more than 5 % cystic glomeruli [97]. ennerz proposed a useful classification system and suggested that the term glomerulocystic kidney disease () is used for the familial subtypes only [98].ype : in 
