yndromic  is when  occurs as part of a known syndrome without dysplasia, the most common being tuberous sclerosis. ther examples include ellweger cerebrohepatorenal syndrome, von ippel indau disease and -linked dominant oral-facial-digital syndrome type 1 (-1).ype :bstructive 
